.Dd June 23, 2026
.Dt TE 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm te
.Nd lightweight text editor with spellchecker, thesaurus and charset conversion
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm te
.Op Ar file
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm te
is a lightweight text editor for Unix-like systems with full UTF-8 support,
multiple charset conversion, configurable colors, undo/redo, search, clipboard,
tab system for editing multiple files, spellchecker, hyphenation, thesaurus,
and editing assistance features.
.Sh INITIAL CONFIGURATION
On first run,
.Nm te
creates a configuration file at
.Pa ~/.tinyedit.conf
in the user's home directory. This file stores editor preferences including
colors, charset settings, wrap mode, line numbers, spellchecker, and editing
assistance features.
.Sh SETUP
The Setup menu (F4 or Alt+T) allows configuration of:
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
Default charset for saving files
.It
Color schemes
.It
Hard/soft wrap mode
.It
Line numbers display
.It
Spellchecker settings (dictionary path, custom dictionary)
.It
Hyphenation settings
.It
Thesaurus settings
.It
Editing assistance toggles (smart quotes, auto-cap, repeated words)
.It
Other editor preferences
.El
.Sh WRAP MODES
.Nm te
supports two wrap modes:
.Bl -enum -compact
.It
Soft-wrap (default): Visual wrapping only, no line breaks inserted
.It
Hard-wrap: Inserts carriage returns at the configured column width
.El
Toggle between modes with Alt+Q.
.Sh TABS
.Nm te
supports editing multiple files simultaneously using a tab system.
Each tab maintains its own editing state, undo history, and cursor position.
.Pp
Alt+J and Alt+K switch between tabs.
Alt+W closes the current tab.
Alt+1-9 and Alt+0 switch to specific tabs.
Press F9 or Alt+L to toggle the tabs panel visibility.
.Sh LINE NUMBERS
Line numbers can be enabled or disabled in Setup (Alt+D toggles).
When enabled, line numbers are displayed in the left margin.
.Sh EDITOR
.Nm te
is a full-featured text editor with spellchecker, hyphenation, thesaurus,
and editing assistance features.
.Ss Spellchecker
.Nm te
includes Hunspell-based spellchecking with support for multiple languages.
.Pp
Spellchecker settings are configured in Setup.
You can enable/disable spellchecking, set the dictionary path, select the dictionary
name (e.g., en_US, es_ES, de_DE, fr_FR), and specify a custom dictionary file.
.Pp
Misspelled words are highlighted in red.
Press Alt+P to check the word under cursor and see suggestions.
Press Enter to accept a suggestion, ESC to cancel.
Press Alt+H to toggle the spell checker panel.
.Ss Hyphenation
.Nm te
supports hyphenation at the hard-wrap column when enabled.
Hyphenation dictionaries follow the LibreOffice format (hyph_*.dic).
Enable in Setup under "Hyphenation" section.
Press Alt+E to toggle hyphen wrap mode.
.Ss Thesaurus
.Nm te
includes thesaurus support (MyThes) for synonym lookup.
Thesaurus dictionaries consist of .idx and .dat files (th_*).
Access with Alt+A to see synonyms for the word under cursor.
.Ss Editing Assistance
.Nm te
provides real-time editing assistance features:
.Bl -enum -compact
.It
Smart quotes: Auto-converts straight quotes to curly quotes based on context
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
Typing ' after a letter becomes closing apostrophe (')
.It
Typing ' after space becomes opening apostrophe (')
.It
Same logic applies to double quotes (" / ")
.El
.It
Auto-cap: Automatically capitalizes the first letter of a word when starting a sentence
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
After . ! or ? followed by space
.It
At document start
.It
After empty line (paragraph separator)
.It
After line ending in . ! or ?
.El
.It
Repeated words: Highlights repeated words in the same line
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
Visual highlight (inverted background) for words like "the the"
.It
Case-insensitive comparison
.El
.El
.Pp
These features can be toggled individually in Setup under "Editor Assistance".
.Sh CHARSET CONVERSION
.Nm te
always works internally with UTF-8. There are two ways to configure charsets:
.Pp
.Bl -enum -compact
.It
Default charset (Setup):
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
Press F4 or Alt+T to open Setup
.It
In the Editor tab, go to the "Charset" field
.It
Press Enter to cycle through available charsets
.It
This will be the charset used by default when saving files
.El
.It
Temporary charset for the current file (F3):
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
Press F3 or Alt+C to change the read/write charset for the current file
.It
Select the read charset (View) and save charset (Save)
.It
If you change the read charset (View), the file is reloaded from disk with the new encoding
.It
If you only change the save charset (Save), the file is not reloaded
.El
.El
.Pp
Available charsets: UTF-8, LATIN-1, LATIN-2, CP437, CP850, CP865, CP866, CP1252
.Sh SEARCH
.Nm te
provides search functionality:
.Bl -enum -compact
.It
Search (F5 or Alt+F):
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
Shows all matches in the document
.It
Navigate between matches with F3/Alt+P (previous) and F4/Alt+N (next)
.El
.It
Find & replace (Ctrl+R):
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
Search and replace text with a popup dialog
.El
.It
Replace all (F6 or Alt+B in search mode):
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
Replace all matches at once
.El
.El
.Pp
Press ESC to exit search mode.
.Sh UNICODE GLYPHS
Press F8 or Alt+U to open the Unicode glyph picker, which allows insertion
of any Unicode character by browsing and selecting from the full Unicode
character set.
.Sh FILE OPERATIONS
Press F7 or Alt+O to insert a file at the cursor position.
.Sh KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS
Basic navigation and editing shortcuts:
.Bl -tag -width "Ctrl+Left/Right"
.It Sy Arrows
Move cursor
.It Sy Home / Ctrl+B
Line start
.It Sy End / Ctrl+E
Line end
.It Sy PgUp / Ctrl+U
Page up
.It Sy PgDn / Ctrl+D
Page down
.It Sy Ctrl+Left/Right
Word left / right
.It Sy Ctrl+Y
Delete line
.It Sy Ctrl+Z
Undo
.It Sy Alt+Z
Redo
.It Sy Ctrl+S
Save
.It Sy ESC / F10
Quit
.El
.Pp
Spellchecker and thesaurus shortcuts:
.Bl -tag -width "Alt+A"
.It Sy Alt+P
Spellcheck word under cursor
.It Sy Alt+H
Toggle spell checker panel
.It Sy Alt+A
Thesaurus lookup
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "~/.tinyedit.conf"
.It Pa ~/.tinyedit.conf
User configuration file
.El
.Sh DICTIONARY FORMATS
.Nm te
uses Hunspell-compatible dictionaries:
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
.aff file: Affix rules and flags
.It
.dic file: Word list with flags
.El
.Pp
Hyphenation dictionaries:
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
hyph_*.dic: Hyphenation patterns (LibreOffice format)
.El
.Pp
Thesaurus dictionaries:
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
th_*.idx: Index file
.It
th_*.dat: Data file with synonym entries
.El
